<h2>Turtles</h2>

<h3>Introduction</h3>

<p>
Turtles are reptiles recognized by the shell that protects their body. They
have existed for millions of years and are among the oldest groups of reptiles
still living today.
</p>

<h3>Different species</h3>

<p>
There are many different kinds of turtles. Some live entirely on land while
others inhabit freshwater or marine environments. Sea turtles are particularly
known for their long migrations across oceans.
</p>

<h3>Diet and lifestyle</h3>

<p>
The diet of turtles varies according to species and habitat. Some are
herbivorous and feed mainly on plants, while others consume insects, fish or
small aquatic animals.
</p>

<h3>Conservation challenges</h3>

<p>
Many turtle species are threatened by habitat destruction, pollution and human
activities. Conservation programs have been developed around the world to help
protect these animals and preserve their natural environments.
</p>
